#: ../../game_variants.rst:10
# 0a5433c5e5d64848bbdab8cbf874d164
msgid "Wizard's Tower"
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:12
# 42b4f65154d1404286b4230f07e42e42
msgid "**A Magic Variant for 2-5 Players.** (Appeared in Theros fat pack booklet.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:14
# a7757df6a1104045a98a24151a5e1b88
msgid "Wizard's Tower is a fun way for you and your friends to explore the set - and everything you need to play is in this fat pack! In this casual format, all players share a single library, also known as the \"Tower,\" and they draft a card in addition to their normal draw for the turn."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:17
# 339809d14b94407994ba6d8633556378
msgid "**Starting the game:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:19
# 742cf71627914de981e22a8312808f4b
msgid "Open the nine booster packs and the land pack in this fat pack. (Try not to look at the cards in the boosters yet, though. It's more fun to discover them during the game.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:21
# 3d31c9d2b68947f4af4b9a03f980311d
msgid "Shuffle all the cards together into a huge deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:22
# 42ce6f59162b4b8e8f74ef52c6f5d996
msgid "Determine randomly who will go first."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:23
# 52f80aa33a9a43f5bd50e1d808d4300f
msgid "Deal three cards to each player."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:24
# a2ee10a87a924d58978ab3df3c7fca9d
msgid "Starting with the first player, each player may discard any number of cards and redraw that many. Once all players have done this, shuffle the discarded cards and put them on the bottom of the deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:26
# b0744f0ea42f48669c0267ab313b1513
msgid "Put the top seven cards of the deck face up in the middle of the table. The deck becomes a library that's shared by all players."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:29
# 22edb3a4ef7d4146b9aa4d270978c5b2
msgid "**Playing the game:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:31
# ee777187b7aa42b19ab06630d90632fc
msgid "When playing Wizard's Tower, your draw step gets a bit more interesting:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:33
# 99ba9236d00b4dd7bacfca7e76ba6bd6
msgid "First, choose one of the face-up cards and add it to your hand. If there aren't any, put the top seven cards of the tower face up in the middle of the table, and then choose one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:36
# d1851bcfabd74b5e97782cdd2972e939
msgid "Draw the top card of the tower."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:37
# 4d1c74bee84c4ca4878c3b605112304f
msgid "All players share the same library and the same graveyard. If you cast a spell that targets a card in an opponent's graveyard or manipulates the top card of your library, those cards affect the shared library or graveyard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:40
# 37e00bce3d854f018fe2f8a393a2cd9e
msgid "The face-up cards aren't considered to be in any game zone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../game_variants.rst:42
# ff861765ecb24b868f7a13ecd34acbdd
msgid "Other than that, the game is played as a Free-for-All **Magic** game. The last player left standing wins!"
msgstr ""

